docs.name: ISE Sentiment Index: Equities
docs.description: The ISE Sentiment Index is a unique put/call value that only uses opening long customer transactions to calculate bullish/bearish market direction. Opening long transactions are thought to best represent market sentiment because investors often buy call and put options to express their actual market view of a particular stock. Market maker and firm trades, which are excluded, are not considered representative of true market sentiment due to their specialized nature. As such, the ISEE calculation method allows for a more accurate measure of true investor sentiment than traditional put/call ratios.

docs.name: SGX 10-Year Mini Japanese Government Bond Futures, June 2015 (JBM2015)
docs.description: Historical Futures Prices: SGX 10-Year Mini Japanese Government Bond Futures, June 2015 (JBM2015), June 2015. The Mini JGB Futures are designed with a unique fungibility mechanism, which allows traders to offset their margins and positions in the JGB futures against the corresponding opposite positions in the Mini JGB Futures, in the ratio of 1 JGB contract to 10 Mini JGB contracts. This mechanism further enhances trading opportunities and provides the most cost-effective deployment of trading capital. Contract Size: ¥10,000,000 notional long term 10-year JGB with 6% coupon. Minimum Price Fluctuation: ¥0.01 per ¥100 face value (¥1,000). Final Settlement Price: Based on the Official Opening Price of TSE's 10-Year JGB futures contract determined from the beginning of their evening session on SGX's Last Trading Day.

docs.name: SGX FTSE China A50 Index Futures, March 2015 (CNH2015)
docs.description: Historical Futures Prices: SGX FTSE China A50 Index Futures, March 2015 (CNH2015), March 2015. SGX China A50 Index Futures is the world’s only offshore futures tracking the A-share market, enabling efficient access into the Chinese growth engine. Tracking the performance of the largest 50 ‘A’ shares companies in China, the underlying FTSE China A50 Index is highly correlated with the domestic Chinese market. Contract Size:	US$ 1 x SGX FTSE  China A50 Index Futures Price. Minimum Price Fluctuation: 5 index point (US$5).

docs.name: SGX MSCI Hong Kong + Index Futures, March 2015 (HKH2015)
docs.description: Historical Futures Prices: SGX MSCI Hong Kong + Index Futures, March 2015 (HKH2015), March 2015. Compiled fully and independently by Morgan Stanley Capital International (MSCI), the MSCI Hong Kong+ IndexSM is market capitalization weighted and has a base date of 31 December 1969 with a value of 100. The MSCI Hong Kong+ IndexSM consists of 42 constituents as of 20 July 2011, and the total full market capitalization is approximately USD760bn. Contract Size: US$5 x MSCI Hong Kong + Index futures price. Minimum Price Fluctuation:	1 index point (US$5). Final Settlement Price: The final settlement price shall be the averaged value of the MSCI Hong Kong + Index, taken at five-minute intervals during the whole day of trading in the underlying stock market on the last trading day. The final settlement price shall be rounded to the nearest one decimal place.
